entries.femaleVariant: Have a seat, V. Be right with you.
You know what to do. Start now.
As we agreed – I got rid of the problem.
I told you to resolve the problem not massacre the European Space Council. Do you understand what the cover-up will cost?
I hate that bitch. I always have.
[Take shard]
Yeah, I think we're clear.
Need your help.
It's what I've collected over the past weeks.
A deep clean. After the shit Frankfurt dumped on us.
I watched the vote. What the hell was that?
Have to handle this voting issue before we lose our bases in the Sea of Clouds.
They're about to begin. What's the situation?
Path of least resistance, always. No nuance. Has you written all over it.
We're not done talking about this.
A datashard?
Proof of my trust.
Go on, take it.
Use this money only, find the right people for the job – no corporate affiliation.
Biometrics, Trauma Team card, names of her closest associates – driver, chief of security, lover, lover's husband. Everything.
Viper pit's putting it lightly.
Need your help, Jack. Got some biz.
<mothertongue l="mex" m="chica" b="Ugh, always biz with you, " a="."/>

entries.femaleVariant: You in some trouble?
Hey, V – you alive? How's things in the viper pit?
Not yet. Just... need a soul I can trust for now.
entries.maleVariant: Not yet. Right now I just need a soul I can trust.

entries.femaleVariant: That kinda sounded like a "yes." Meet me at Lizzie's. Be there in an hour.
Are you sure this is a good idea?
I have a few questions.
Uh, regarding the--
Listen, I--
Take this.
Now she's holding a gun to my head to make sure I don't try anything.
What would you do in my position?
Visitor authorization granted.
Emergency protocols active. System security confirmed.
We would've lost the license, now we gained a week. That's a win.
But she won't pull the trigger because she needs me. I do what she doesn't have the guts to do.
You have to defend yourself. Remind Abernathy you're not her doormat.
You need to defend yourself.
There's not much you can do. She's got the Night City board on her side. If she wants you out, well... you understand.
Seems we see eye to eye on this issue.
Not much you can do.
You're right.
Smack her once... but hard. She'll respect you.
I do.
You said it. I need to defend myself.
Said it yourself – she's left me no choice.
This is a huge gamble.
What'll happen if I refuse?
If anyone finds out we even talked about this... I'll go down with you.
Don't ask stupid questions.
This isn't a request, V.
And if I refuse?
That's true. But everyone knows you only made it to where you are thanks to me.
So it's not like they could ever believe you played no part in it.
We seem to understand each other. Take this, too.
And for the core task... use someone you know inside out. Are we clear?
In that case, I'll await your report. And good luck with it.
Use it. And make sure Abernathy won't be a problem anymore.
Director Abernathy.
Divide and conquer. Effective strategy.
I have my AV waiting outside. It's yours to use.
Are you online?
Affirmative. Online and in their system. No sign we've been detected.
Can you get access to their preliminary declarations?
They usually stick to them. It should give us a good overview.
Yes. On it…
Pff, "effective"...
Have you worked together long?
This isn't the first time Abernathy's set you up.
entries.maleVariant: This... isn't the first time Abernathy's set you up.

entries.femaleVariant: "Always," meaning how long?
It's not the first time she's screwed you.
Before Night City we worked on an assignment in Osaka. Two years of subterfuge. She spent them digging a trap for me.
When she became Director of Spec Ops, that's when she finally shoved me in it.
Smeared me in front of Japanese execs so she'd be the one promoted to Director of Spec Ops. The cunt.
No, not the first...
Honestly?
Please.
[Take money]
Credchip transactions are traceable... paper disappears as soon as you spend it.
entries.maleVariant: Credchip transactions are traceable… heh, paper disappears as soon as you spend it.

entries.femaleVariant: What can I say.
Good...
Viper pit. Couldn'ta said it better.
Jenkins, Night City counterintel.
I need an analysis of the legislative procedures for lunar base licenses.
Yes. Yes, the Sea of Clouds.
Black clinics. Operating outside earthly jurisdiction.
No, not yet. We're just exploring options for now.
On the authority of Director Abernathy, yes...
Of course, unofficially.
[Sit]
[Stand]
Please enter the antechamber.
And don't disappoint me.
Uh-huh… Yeah, if that's how it's got to be.
That's clear… hmm.
Say again?
We need to talk.
Mhm... Yeah, just as we thought.
Mhh...
A datashard?
Can't go wrong with cash.
